Want to be part of our team? Join now.



MusMe opens the doors to composers.

Our team is very open-minded and will listen to your suggestions and advice.

We don’t have any restrictions regarding the style or genre of music you create, but please keep in mind that we only accept high quality material, both in terms of musical structure and recording/production.

Audio File should be cleanly recorded and professionally prepared, in the highest quality possible. The music/audio file should have an aesthetic value and should be useful for media purposes. All of the submitted files are reviewed by our team before appearing on the marketplace. The review procedure takes a maximum of 12 days (usually within a week).

Due to the large number of submissions to the library, all new accounts are allowed to submit up to three music/audio files and wait for the review process to pass successfully before submitting more files. This is a one-time procedure that will be easy to pass for most of the authors and will help us to maintain the highest quality across the TwinsMusic Enterprises marketplace.

File Size

Files should be no larger than 100MB and must be sent as downloadable files to twinsmusicny@yahoo.com via WeTransfer.

File Format

All files should be high-quality WAV files (16 Bit, 44.1 kHz).

Please check your files before uploading to make sure they are high-quality and broadcast-ready. After uploading, your item is inspected and checked by our review team to ensure that it is suitable for the marketplace.

Ownership

You must be the copyright-owner for any audio you make available for licensing.

Ownership must be 100% in order to be eligible for the TwinsMusic Enterprises catalog.

Legal Issues

As an author you have the responsibility to only sell things that belong to you. By selling an item, you are making an agreement not only with TwinsMusic Enterprises but with anyone who buys your item that you own full copyright to that item, and have appropriately licensed any content that it makes use of.

Transactions are between you and the purchaser. If you are doing something wrong (e.g. breaching copyright), you are responsible and liable. TwinsMusic Enterprises has the right to remove the item or permanently ban the author if there are multiple instances of copyright issues.

Licenses

When you sell an item on TwinsMusic Enterprises you are granting a buyer a license to use the item. There are two types of licenses:

  • MusMe Moods Library sold in an annual subscription.
  • A Standard License which is sold on a per item basis.

Pricing

The cost of each item is decided by our team during the review by complexity, duration and quality. You can suggest the price during the upload (by adding a note for reviewer) but it’s not guaranteed that the audio file will be sold at your suggested price.

Payment Rate

Non-exclusive authors will receive the following payment percentages for their work:

  • 50% of the revenue sold for single song licensing.
  • 50% of the revenue we collect from our MusMe Moods Library, based on the number of downloads for an author’s song.

Withdrawals

You can request a withdrawal of earnings from your account once you have reached a threshold of $50 or more.

We require you to submit a copy of Passport/ID-card and W-9/W-8BEN form before we accept a withdrawal request. It’s a one-time procedure.

Acceptable payment method include:

  • PayPal
  • Wire transfer
  • Credit Card

Withdrawals requested during the current month are completed by the 15-th of the following month (i.e. if you request the withdrawal in September, you will receive your funds on October 15-th).

); } export default Submit;
